            <h2> Enugu State</h2>
            <blockquote>

                2 Hatcheries with total Capacity of 250,000 doc/day
                Intervention of CADP led to establishment of first ever poultry hatchery in South East Zone of Nigeria located in Enugu (Sunchi Integrated Farms Ltd). Before now, poultry farmers in that Zone sourced their day old chicks from Lagos and Ibadan in the South West Zone. 500 farmers from around the South East Zone, Kano, Kaduna and Abuja have been linked to Sunchi Integrated Farms as off-takers of Day Old Chicks (DOCs). The company’s capacity has risen from a capacity of 5,072 day old chicks per week when it commenced operation to the current capacity of 55,000 day old chick per week. A second Hatchery has since joined the train in Enugu State also.

            </blockquote>
