        <h2>
            Kano
        </h2>
        <blockquote>
            A dairy farmer, Messrs Bunkure Farms, benefitted from demonstration and adoption of artificial insemination of 98 local heifers using semen from disease resistant and early maturing breed and within a year, 86 of the heifers were harvested. The harvested bulls were subsequently artificially inseminated to produce second generation 50% hybrid. This achievement has prompted the entrepreneur to go into construction of a 12-point industrial milking facility. The farm has also turned to demonstration centre for other farmers in Kano State wishing to grow their farm through the new artificial insemination technology.
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote>
            In order to facilitate sustainable market access for the project beneficiaries, thirty three (33) CIGs in Kano State have been linked to Abuja Security and Commodity Exchange on improved marketing system and warehousing financing. Another eleven (11) benefitting CIGs were linked to an off-taker, UMZA Rice Processing Company, to which they have already supplied a total of 240.89mt of rice paddy as contract out-growers
        </blockquote>
